        description: `A Malkuth-class reactor is the baseline mana generation unit issued to newly awakened mages under the Star Light Project. Its single-layer crystalline core holds 1x capacity — the reference point against which all higher ranks are measured. Full depletion requires 8-12 minutes of ambient absorption to recover, and the reactor can sustain only one concurrent spell effect reliably, two if neither exceeds Tier 2 complexity. Spell routines above Tier 3 exceed the core's throughput ceiling, causing mana bleed that wastes roughly thirty percent of each casting as radiant heat.

In practical terms, a Malkuth mage operates under constant resource scarcity. A single Tier 3 combat spell consumes a quarter of total reserves, limiting engagement to 2-3 full-power casts per cycle before mandatory recovery. The single lamination structure provides no buffering against draw spikes, which forces most Malkuth mages to develop precise mana discipline — smooth, controlled casting with minimal waste. Field instructors note that mages who spend extensive time at this rank often outperform higher-ranked peers in efficiency metrics, having learned habits that treat every joule of mana as precious.

The unique capability at Malkuth is also its vulnerability: the reactor's simplicity makes it remarkably stable against mana feedback, virtually immune to the resonance cascades that plague multi-layer cores, but this same lack of internal buffering means any disruption to the casting process dumps the full spell cost as waste. Interrupted casts at Malkuth rank bleed mana directly into the environment, a failure mode that can leave the mage depleted after a single botched routine.`
